### ğŸ’£ Sideloading Risk

High.  
- Communication is often claimed as â€œsuccessfulâ€ when only power has been exerted or noise has been repeated. This hides the **failure of comprehension** or **consent**.

Invalid examples:
- â€œWe communicated our decision clearly.â€ â†’ But if the receiver had no interpretive access (due to jargon, language, exclusion), it wasnâ€™t communication.
- â€œThe law is public, so people are informed.â€ â†’ Visibility â‰  comprehensibility; mere presence doesnâ€™t equal meaningful communication.

